data.title: CCS Announces 2022-23 Academic All-Conference
data.meta_description: BRANDON, Miss. – Collegiate Conference of the South Commissioner Beth Vansant released the league’s inaugural Academic All-Conference listing for 2022-23, recognizing student-athletes with at least a 3.30 grade-point average.
data.text:
Includes 157 on Presidents’ Honor Roll

BRANDON, Miss. – Collegiate Conference of the South Commissioner Beth Vansant released the league’s inaugural Academic All-Conference listing for 2022-23, recognizing student-athletes with at least a 3.30 grade-point average.

“It’s an honor to recognize our inaugural list of Academic All-Conference and Presidents’ Honor Roll student-athlete recipients,” said Vansant. “Our conference values exceptional athletics competition along with the outstanding work that occurs in the classroom. It is the NCAA Division III model, and we are proud of our first class of Academic All-Conference honorees.”

This was the inaugural season for the Collegiate Conference of the South, which features nine NCAA Division III institutions in Alabama, Georgia, Kentucky, Mississippi and Tennessee.

A total of 721 honorees earned at least a 3.30 grade-point average in each semester of the 2022-23 academic year. Those 158 shown with an asterisk (*) beside their name earned placement on the Presidents’ Honor Roll after posting at least a cumulative 3.90 GPA for the academic year. Honorees were selected from the conference's 14 championship sports.
